<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Ehostunreach on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/ehostunreach/</link><description>Recent content in Ehostunreach on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/ehostunreach/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C errno EHOSTUNREACH — No route to host Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-ehostunreach/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-ehostunreach/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-errno-ehostunreach--no-route-to-host-fix"&gt;[Solution] C errno EHOSTUNREACH — No route to host Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When a network operation fails because the destination host is unreachable (no route exists or the host is not responding), the system call sets &lt;code&gt;errno&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;EHOSTUNREACH&lt;/code&gt;. This error indicates the kernel cannot find a path to the target host.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No route exists to the target host&amp;rsquo;s network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The default gateway is not configured or is unreachable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A firewall rule drops packets to the target, causing ICMP unreachable responses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The target host is on a different subnet and the gateway is down.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Verify routing configuration and gateway availability. Check firewall rules.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C No route to host: EHOSTUNREACH</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/host-unreachable/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/host-unreachable/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="no-route-to-host-ehostunreach"&gt;No route to host: EHOSTUNREACH&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EHOSTUNREACH occurs when a specific host cannot be reached. Unlike ENETUNREACH (no route to network), this means a route exists but the host itself is unreachable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Host is down
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;connect&lt;/span&gt;(sock, (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; sockaddr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;addr, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(addr)); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EHOSTUNREACH
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Firewall blocking (ICMP reject)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// iptables rule rejecting packets to host
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Wrong IP address
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// DNS resolved to wrong IP
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-verify-host-is-reachable"&gt;Fix 1: Verify host is reachable&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ping target_host
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;traceroute target_host
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-check-firewall-rules"&gt;Fix 2: Check firewall rules&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;iptables -L -n | grep DROP
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# or&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;nft list ruleset
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-check-dns-resolution"&gt;Fix 3: Check DNS resolution&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;nslookup target_host
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;dig target_host
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/network-unreachable/"&gt;Network unreachable&lt;/a&gt; — ENETUNREACH.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/connection-refused-c/"&gt;Connection refused&lt;/a&gt; — ECONNREFUSED.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/operation-timed-out/"&gt;Connection timed out&lt;/a&gt; — ETIMEDOUT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C No route to host: EHOSTUNREACH</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/no-route-to-host-c/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/no-route-to-host-c/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="no-route-to-host-ehostunreach"&gt;No route to host: EHOSTUNREACH&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EHOSTUNREACH occurs when a route to the destination host cannot be found. This is different from ENETUNREACH which means no route to the network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Host is unreachable
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;connect&lt;/span&gt;(sock, (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; sockaddr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;addr, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(addr)); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EHOSTUNREACH
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Wrong subnet
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Host is on different subnet without gateway
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Host is down
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Target machine powered off
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-routing-table"&gt;Fix 1: Check routing table&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ip route show
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# or&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;route -n
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-add-route"&gt;Fix 2: Add route&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ip route add 10.0.0.0/24 via 192.168.1.1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-verify-host-is-up"&gt;Fix 3: Verify host is up&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ping target_host
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;arping target_host
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/network-unreachable/"&gt;Network unreachable&lt;/a&gt; — ENETUNREACH.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/connection-refused-c/"&gt;Connection refused&lt;/a&gt; — ECONNREFUSED.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/operation-timed-out/"&gt;Connection timed out&lt;/a&gt; — ETIMEDOUT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux EHOSTUNREACH (errno 77) — No Route to Host Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-77/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-77/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-ehostunreach-errno-77--no-route-to-host"&gt;Linux EHOSTUNREACH (errno 77) — No Route to Host&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EHOSTUNREACH (errno 77) means there is no route to the target host. This error occurs when the system cannot determine how to reach a specific remote host, even though the network itself is up. It is distinct from ENETUNREACH (errno 65) because EHOSTUNREACH refers to a specific host, while ENETUNREACH refers to an entire network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No route exists to the destination host&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gateway does not know how to reach the host&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Host is on a different network with no routing path&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Static route is missing or misconfigured&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix-ehostunreach"&gt;How to Fix EHOSTUNREACH&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-routing-table"&gt;1. Check Routing Table&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Verify routes to the destination:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>